#### House of Representatives

The [House of Representatives](/United_States_House_of_Representatives) also saw its composition evolve significantly during the [2nd Congress](/2nd_United_States_Congress). The admission of [Vermont](/Vermont) and [Kentucky](/Kentucky) led to the allocation of two new House seats for each state, expanding the body's overall size and introducing new regional perspectives into the national legislature. (Sess. 3, ch. 9, 1&#160;[Stat.](/United_States_Statutes_at_Large)&#160;191). The ebb and flow of elections, resignations, and contested results painted a picture of a dynamic and responsive representative body, even in these early years.

